                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.124A/20: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wharton</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-12-27T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 27, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>57. Your December 23, 6 p.m. Form of Article 3 as changed by Barclay
                    satisfactory.</p>
                <p>For your information Dr. Smith of Public Health Service sails for Monrovia from
                    Rotterdam on January 3.<note n="47" xml:id="d363fn47">Arrived at Monrovia on
                        January 20, 1930. His appointment was approved by President Hoover on
                        December 5, 1929.</note> (See Department’s telegram No. 37, October 8, 1929,
                    Paragraph 5 (<hi rend="italic">e</hi>).)</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
